<br>
What is really so bad about those items showing up in general?<br>
<br>
The more in depth questions will be answered (sometimes repeatidly) in the more specific forums. If someone happens to come across the definitive answer to a question, backed up with pages of proof and an iron clad answer and they happen to post it in general ... too bad for them if it slides off the first page too fast. <br>
<br>
Perhaps a mod could move that definitive answer thread to the proper place, but other wise I've always seen &quot;general&quot; forums as the junk drawer in my house. Jammed full of stuff, and a lot it redundant to other things in the house (pens, lightbulbs, bateries, tools, etc.) It's kind of handy to have easy access to some of those things, but if I find something in there that belongs in it's &quot;proper place&quot; (pliers back into the toolbox, pens back into the office, etc.) then I put it there.<br>
<br>
I don't mean to over step my bounds, being new and all, and I think the moderation here has been great.<br>
<br>
I peruse General each time I come and hit the specific forums when I am looking for something ... well ... specific.<br>
<br>
Board newbies will post in General but eventually learn that they are better served for specific questions in the specific fourms.<br>
<br>
My suggestion would be to let us have our junk drawer, let us mention to you when we have a really good thread that might be better off in a specific forum (so you don't have to constantly keep checking all the threads), and let the general messages just drop off the first page if folks post a lot.<br>
<br>
I think it might aleviate a lot of stress for the mods.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 copper.<br>
