<br>
A messageboard is not the same as a website.  There is something to be said for having the information being easily accesible and indexed, but there is also something to be sad for having an open forum to discuss things. <br>
<br>
When someone posts a question, even if the answer is availiable via a search, a new discussion of the topic can take new directions and yield new information.  Moreover, I like being able to help out someone who has a question I know the answer to.  I like a good debate. I like interaction.<br>
<br>
Right now you seem to view this messageboard as some type of mage database.  That's may be a good project for you, but right now you are spending an inordinate amount of time policing the members of a community that may or may not have the same goals or desires as you.  <br>
<br>
